{"key":"processedPost-9560801","value":{"id":9560801,"first":9560723,"last":9563313,"when":1231303615,"utime":"01/07/09 06:46 AM","content":"I think you'll find that alternating layers will work better than a thorough mixing.&nbsp; Be sure to have a top layer of straight manure with no grains showing on the surface.&nbsp; The reason is that when you layer the spawn, it seems to knit back together faster than with individual kernels infiltrating the manure.&nbsp; However you mix the spawn and bulk substrate, leave a layer of bulk on top as said.&nbsp; When grains are left exposed on top, contamination sets in much easier.<br />RR","title":"Re: how do you mix your spawn and subs????","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}